genresAdvancedInfo.name: guatemalan metal
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A heavy and aggressive music genre that emerged in the 1990s and has since become a popular subculture in Guatemala. Guatemalan metal is known for its loud and distorted guitar riffs, pounding drum beats, and intense vocals that often touch on themes of social and political injustice. It is typically performed by bands who prioritize technical proficiency and a high-energy live performance.
